ign=left class=m><span class=title> Does a cleric get boring?</span><hr size=1> I'm trying to picture myself playing a cleric and all i see myself doing is medding, stand up to heal, then sit back down to med, etc, etc...<br>
<br>
Does it ever change? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/beqasylum.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ash>Ash</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fire Beetle</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/16/00 8:17:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Does a cleric get boring?</span><hr size=1> it changes depending on the way you want to play.. mainly during raids and tough fights thats the best way to play.  but clerics have a very versatile spell list, we not only heal but stun, buff, root &amp; peel, play aggro shield (love divine aura spells <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) and dare i say cough*melee*cough.  Just how you want to play your char.  but note that depending on how you play (i.e. not medding to heal etc) others will judge you for it.  But in the end so long as you are keeping your party healthy who are they to judge? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src=http://eqscreenshot.homestead.com/files/fire1.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaindiacrimsonwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aindia Crimsonwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fire Beetle</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/16/00 8:55:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Does a cleric get boring?</span><hr size=1> Well it depends on how ya look at a cleric - our job is to buff and keep our party members alive. We do whatever we have to to do that.  Whether it be peel and park, or nuke or whatever.   I mainly (99% of the time) just buff, heal and stun mobs.  Depending on the party, if I don't have to heal much and I've got plenty of mana I will melee upon occassion as well.   But all in all you can't forget what your MAIN reason for being in a group is.. you keep them alive.  And like Ashes said - your reputation (for future grouping etc) depends on how you perform. If ya nuke a lot and don't have mana to heal, you're less likely to be wanted for groups...but there are times when you are allowed to be a wanna be wizard <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   As you get higher in levels you will find what works best for you.  <br>
<br>
But after a while clerics can get boring...I won't kid you on that.  In my 40's I almost quit, and I think almost every cleric goes thru a phase at some point when they get tired of the heal sit heal routine.  It happens to us all at some point, but we love our class, and we love what we do so we keep on doing it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p><p align=center><b><font size=4><font color=crimson>~Aindia Crimsonwind~</b></font><br><font size=2>51st Cleric of Tunare</font><br><b><font size=2>Member of     <a href=http://geocities.com/thechosenclan target="web">The Chosen Clan</a></font></b></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uisyssreigns.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Isyss Reigns</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fire Beetle</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/17/00 12:13:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Does a cleric get boring?</span><hr size=1> I agree, there are times when playing a cleric does get to you in terms of boredom, but once you get those difficult areas in dugeons, and more interesting strategies to use. Like as everyone said, it'll depends on how you play your cleric and it does take a certain mentality to be one. As you get higher, things change for the better and more rewarding. So hang in there, phases comes and goes.<br>
