 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufelishannasecretlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felishanna Secretlight</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/19/00 3:17:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Does a cleric get boring?</span><hr size=1> An interesting thread. What lies behind this question is what probably many non-clerics will not realise. A cleric does spend a vast proportion of her (I'll use feminine pronouns throughout, but masculine equally apply) time medding, but during that time, she should be watching the ebbs and flows of battle carefully, and managing her mana output and the various heals/buffs she is using carefully so as at time of need, there is best chance of keeping someone alive where otherwise they would die. This is something largely invisible to other party members, but it is crucial to keeping a good party running in a tight situation.<br>
<br>
Of course, a good back-up healer and a puller who listens to the cleric mana call before pulling are key elements to add to this. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Is this boring? Depends on your playstyle and what you enjoy. For me, the answer is, most certainly not! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
